What is the difference between for loop and while loop? ( in terms of syntax and working )

/* While loop syntax */

initialization;

while(condition)
{
    // body

    update;
}



/* For loop syntax */

for(initialization; condition; update)
{
    // body
}


Working is same for both.
1) initialization
2) check condition
3) body ( execute each block of stmt )
4) update
